課程概述 Course Description
       世界是一個離散的系統。然而“連續”的理念已成功地描述各種現象。 研究高溫等離子體，其平均自由程比系統的特點長度更長，這是一個很好的起點，重新審視流體，說明在何種程度上可以有效的。 在這個課程中，重點將放在連續的基本流體動力學 [例如：Lagrangian 與 Eulerian 變量。 耗散流體中的保守屬性，耗散和壓縮角色，波不穩定性 ] 進階主題是，保形映射，邊界層理論，非線性波[Burgers，KdV，非線性 Schroedinger 方程，衝擊波，例如，進行 了討論。大約有 25％的材料將包括磁流體。 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
Real world is made out of discrete points. See why idea of continua works.Waves, instabilities, and turbulence in neutral fluids and plasmas.  
Advanced topics, shocks, boundary layer theory, nonlinear waves.
 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
12/25 Introduction to mechanics of continua.
23/3 From Klimontovich equation to Boltzmann equation.
33/10 From Boltzmann equation to fluid equations.43/17 Inviscid fluid (Euler's equation) and Kelvin's circulation theorem. Bernoulli's principle.
53/24 Sound waves in fluids.
63/31 Holiday (no class). Mid term scheduled out of regular class.
74/7 Sound waves and Shocks.
84/14 Raleigh-Taylor instability. 94/21 Kelvin-Helmholtz instability.
104/28 Origin of viscosity and turbulence.115/5 Navier-Stokes equation and boundary layer theory.125/12 Shallow water surface waves. Tsunami and solitons.
135/19 Ion acoustic wave and solitons.


145/26 Langmuir wave and solitons.156/2 Langmuir solitons and Nonlinear Schroedinger equation.166/9 Holiday (no class).176/16 Wave breaking.186/23 Final exam. 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


